modules.description: Generates randomized test inputs by mutating existing data using probabilistic rules. Operates on byte sequences and strings, applying transformations such as insertion, deletion, and substitution. Used to stress-test parsers and input handlers with varied, unpredictable data.

Generates mutated versions of input strings using a randomized algorithm, with optional seed control for reproducibility. Operates on raw string data to produce variations suitable for testing or fuzzing. Used to create diverse test cases by altering existing input patterns.
